description:
Abraham is called out of a thriving city to go to a place where he did not know. Visit archaeological sites where Abraham visited and pitched his tents. Learn about all that Abraham's journey required him to leave behind as he obediently listened to the voice of God. Because of Abraham's faith we can receive the gospel today. Francois DuPlessis shows pictures of the sites where Abraham visited when he left his comfortable city for an unknown and uncomfortable journey following God.

Watch more: https://adtv.watch/

Subscribe to our YouTube channel: https://www.youtube.com/user/OfficialADTVChannel?sub_confirmation=1

Visit our website: https://new.amazingdiscoveries.org/

chapters.title: What about Terah, Abram's father? Did he climb the steps of the Urnamu to worship the moon god?
Inside a traditional house of Haran
Whom of Abram's family moved with him to Haran?
Amazing discoveries at Aleppo shed new light on the story of the Bible.
Caravan Sarai - resting place for camel caravans
Dangerous ancient roads winding through foreign far places.
Are these ruins of Tyre found in the ocean?
